NO, I am NOT ruling out HARNESS racing, but TROTTERS are not referred to as 'racehorses'  usually--being very differently trained and raced.  Seeing that word in a clue sends most people's minds straight to The Derby, Preakness, and Belmont, for example.  

Indiana has a pretty robust harness-racing tradition, and if we hark back to "The Music Man," we hear someone exclaiming over horse-racing "where they sit right down on the horse!"

